<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There is so much incorrect information about this mob (and about the SK Epic) that I'd like to take a moment to give you a few indisputable facts so that all questions (and typical message board flames) can end: <br>
<br>
Lhranc has 2 basic forms that he can take: the first being his standard undead form found in CoM (Level 61 SK).  He will do about 260 hp dmg (can go up to 350) and can lifetap for 500 (and will do so randomly). He can boil blood and cascade darkness but doesn't do so often. He has a truckload of HP and despite some ridiculous claims, cannot be solo'd or even killed by one group for that matter. In this form, he's about a 3 group mob and a tough one. <br>
<br>
His other form is &quot;Ressurected&quot; which occurs at the completion of the SK Epic (which is not ninja lootable in any way nor has it been despite some people's claims). You gain a token from Lhranc which you then hand to Marl after Lhranc dies (if Lhranc dies). In his ressurected form, Lhranc is Level 63, does approx. 350+ hp damage (doubles constantly), lifetaps for his usual 500 and CAN death touch though this is infrequent at best (only seen it on one raid of 3). He does dot and his HP is massive: he takes generally 4+ good groups to bring him down though most SK's bring 5 or 6 groups to be safe (and realize most of these will die but 1 or 2 groups will be left standing after tge carnage) as he has a nasty habit of lifetapping like a madman when he hits 1/3 life. He is fairly magic resistant (resists alot of the bloodline and can't be feared) but can be cast on using some DD spells. <br>
<br>
He is a human..not an iksar or sarnak and is a Shadowknight but doesn't employ Harm Touch as you'd expect (thank Innoruk for that...his HT would be MASSIVE). <br>
<br>
EPIC STRATEGY: As the SK finalizing your epic, allow someone else to pull and another to main tank...you dont want to be on the firing line right away because he'll kill the first 3 he faces down more than likely. Send in your pet on him as well and hang back long enough for someone to draw aggro..your pet won't do enough damage to pull his wrath but will do 35-50 a hit (sucks but hey Lhranc is mean and every little bit helps). Don't bother casting dots as nothing you throw at him will stock (he resists bloodline VERY well). Make sure that your party not only has plentiful healers and tanks but also a good amount of wizards as some of their DD's land on him nicely. Keep a shield equipped and BASH constantly (or SLAM if you are also able) as he can be interrupted. If you are above level 58, use discipline unholyaura and employee your Harm Touch when he's below 1/4 (sooner than that will seal your fate). His lifetap hurts but if everyone has been Aego'd, you'll survive it with nothing but a scare and a red gone. CoM is a bindable city fort most classes so do so: he's bound to kill many.<br>
